UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1549
1 AN ACT relating to immunizations.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 214.034 is amended to read as follows:
4 Except as otherwise provided in KRS 214.036:
5 (1) All parents, guardians, and other persons having care, custody, or control of any
6 child shall have the child immunized against diphtheria, tetanus, poliomyelitis,
7 pertussis, measles, rubella, mumps, [hepatitis B, ]and haemophilis influenzae
8 disease in accordance with testing and immunization schedules established by
9 regulations of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services. Additional
10 immunizations shall not[may] be required by the Cabinet for Health and Family
11 Services through the promulgation of an administrative regulation pursuant to KRS
12 Chapter 13A without the approval of the General Assembly[if recommended by
13 the United States Public Health Service or the American Academy of Pediatrics].
14 All parents, guardians, and other persons having care, custody, or control of any
15 child shall also have any child found to be infected with tuberculosis examined and
16 treated according to administrative regulations of the Cabinet for Health and Family
17 Services promulgated under KRS Chapter 13A. The persons shall also have booster
18 immunizations administered to the child in accordance with the regulations of the
19 Cabinet for Health and Family Services.
20 (2) A local health department may, with the approval of the Department of Public
21 Health, require all first-time enrollees in a public or private school within the health
22 department's jurisdiction to be tested for tuberculosis prior to entering school.
23 Following the first year of school, upon an epidemiological determination made by
24 the state or local health officer in accordance with administrative regulations
25 promulgated by the Cabinet for Health and Family Services, all parents, guardians,
26 and other persons having care, custody, or control of any child shall have the child
27 tested for tuberculosis, and shall have any child found to be infected with
